column2: Has the student written a compelling opening?
column4: Has the student used a range of literary devices?
column5: Has the student made an effort to create dynamic characters?
column6: Has the student established a sense of setting?
column7: Has the student varied their sentence structure?
column8: Has the student varied their sentence length?
column9: Has the student written a story that follows the narrative arc?
column10: Has the student engaged with the prompt?
column12: Has the student followed the rules of using dialogue? (1. speech marks 2. new speaker new line 3. punctuation before closing speech marks 4. speech tags).
column14: Has the student used the five senses in their writing?
